 The Financial Times

 
 
 CHANNEL FIVE BOSS TO STEP DOWN Channel Five Chairman and Chief Executive Dawn Airey is set
to leave the broadcaster to join RTL, in a move expected to
indicate a shake-up at the company.
here UK SCIENTISTS DEVELOP TEST TO DIAGNOSE AUTISM
British scientists have developed a 15-minute brain scan
that could in future be used to test for autism, helping doctors
diagnose the complex condition more cheaply and accurately.
here 
 BP SPILL SUITS TO BE HEARD IN U.S. Companies involved in the Gulf of Mexico oil spil, including
BP (BP.L), will face scores of damages lawsuits launched against
them by a judicial panel to be heard in New Orleans.
here FED DOWNGRADES RECOVERY OUTLOOK The U.S. Federal Reserve downgraded its view of the economic
outlook amid fears of a double-dip recession, saying the "pace
of recovery in output and employment has slowed in recent
months."
here 
  FUND INVESTOR IN BREACH OF CONTRACT
  Melrose Resources (MRS.L) Chairman Robert Adair has breached a
contract by refusing to put more money into Advantage Capital's
buyout fund, a High Court ruled in an unprecedented move.
here REPSOL'S IPO OF BRAZILIAN UNIT ON TRACK Spain's oil and gas group Repsol YPF (REP.MC) is on track
for an initial public offering of its Brazilian operations
valued at about $4 billion.
